dcterms:creator: A. Jesson
S. Mindermann
Y. Gal
U. Shalit
dcterms:description: The IHDP dataset is a hidden confounding version of the Infant Health and Development Program, which includes synthetic potential outcomes generated according to a specific response surface. It is used to study the effects of treatment on low-birth-weight, premature infants, with hidden confounding introduced by excluding certain covariates from the training models.
dcterms:title: IHDP (Infant Health and Development Program) Hidden Confounding

dcterms:creator: V. Chernozhukov
C. Hansen
dcterms:description: The 401(k) Eligibility Dataset examines the effects of 401(k) participation on the wealth distribution, utilizing data from the 1991 Survey of Income and Program Participation. It focuses on the relationship between 401(k) eligibility and net financial assets.
dcterms:title: 401(k) Eligibility Dataset
